article.headline: Bowling Green 59, Wright State 56
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- Martin Samarco scored 22 points Saturday night to lead Bowling Green to a 59-56 win over Wright State. The Falcons trailed by one point with 1:08 left until Ryne Hamblet hit a 3-pointer, pulling Bowling Green ahead 55-53. Darryl Clements then made all four of his free throw attempts in the final seconds to preserve the lead. Dusan Radivojevic added 12 points for the Falcons (5-3), the only other Bowling Green player in double figures. DaShaun Wood led Wright State (3-5) with 23 points. Vaughn Duggins scored 11 points and Jordan Pleiman added 10. Bowling Green shot 53 percent from the field, while Wright State, which led 34-30 at halftime, shot just 30 percent.
